title: Tony Mizen - The Baroque Ukulele
description: Classical ukulele player Tony Mizen has arranged 22 of the best-loved pieces from the Baroque era for reentrant GCEA tuning. This includes well-known works by J.S. Bach, Corelli, Handel, Pachelbel, Purcell and even an entire concerto by Vivaldi. All arrangements feature ukulele tablature and standard notation. Includes an overview of the music of the Baroque era and notes on each of the individual pieces. The CD contains beautiful performances of all of the arrangements by Mizen.
